To setup the Terraform statefile
Prior to this, setup user/profile and granular policies should be assigned to the user.

Step 1: Create s3 bucket 
 	aws s3 mb s3://<bucket_name>

Step 2: Step 3: Initialize terraform 
	terraform init

Step 3: Create variables for profile and region

Step 4: Create AWS provider 

Step 5: Run the following commands.
	terraform init
	terraform fmt
	terraform validate
	terraform plan
	terraform apply

Step 6: Deploy VPC, subnets & IGW

Step 7: Create security groups to allow TCP/80 and SSH/22 connections

Step 8: Fetch the AMI id using SSM Parameter store

Step 9: Deploy EC2-key pair
Consider using Secret Manager - Parameter Store to store key-pair
    ssh-keygen -t rsa 

Step 10: Deploy EC2-Instance
Step 11: Create an output file to fetch ec2-instance public_ip




 
